Blockchain System Overview (Short Version)
1. Smart Contracts (Ethereum)
Store metadata: IPFS hash, patient ID, uploader’s address, and timestamp.

Serve as public audit logs and optional access controllers.

Example Functions:

uploadFile(patientId, ipfsHash) → stores metadata and emits an event.

getFiles(patientId) → retrieves all files for a patient.

Optional: Emit events for file views or maintain an access log.

Solidity Snippet:

solidity
Copy
Edit
struct File {
    string ipfsHash;
    address uploader;
    uint256 timestamp;
}
mapping(string => File[]) public patientFiles;

function uploadFile(string memory patientId, string memory ipfsHash) public {
    patientFiles[patientId].push(File(ipfsHash, msg.sender, block.timestamp));
}
2. IPFS (InterPlanetary File System)
Stores actual documents (PDFs, test results, etc.).

Returns a content-addressed hash (CID)—a unique fingerprint of the file.

CID changes if even 1 byte of the file is altered, allowing verifiability.

Optional: Encrypt files with AES/RSA before uploading for additional privacy.

3. Ethereum Blockchain
Acts as a public, immutable ledger.

Logs all metadata transactions permanently and securely.

Uses Proof of Stake (PoS) for consensus.

Each action requires gas; testnets like Sepolia are used to avoid real costs.

Optionally migrate to Polygon or another Layer 2 for scalability.

4. Metamask Integration
Allows hospital staff to log in via their Ethereum wallet.

All file uploads and actions are signed by the user, ensuring traceability.

Metamask ensures non-repudiation—each transaction has a digital signature.

Optional Advanced Features

Feature	Description
Role-based Access	Restrict functions to roles like doctor or admin using Solidity modifiers.
Event Logging	Emit events for every record access to create an access trail.
Chainlink Timestamping	Use Chainlink oracles for trusted external timestamps.
Zero-Knowledge Proofs	Mention ZKPs to maintain privacy while proving access/authentication.
Multi-signature Uploads	Require multiple sign-offs for uploading sensitive records.